If you keep having me around,

280
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:44,460
I can show you even cooler places.

281
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:48,460
What are you planning to do?

282
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:50,460
Why do you want to be
here when it's closed?

283
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:55,980
You scared?

284
00:18:57,470 --> 00:18:58,760
Doesn't sound like you.

285
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:02,510
As if I ever get scared.

286
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:37,370
That was close.

287
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:42,130
You sure love risky things.

288
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:08,960
Wait here.

289
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:39,660
What's this?

290
00:20:40,170 --> 00:20:42,940
You wanted to bowl so
bad you became a burglar?

291
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:44,670
No.

292
00:20:47,860 --> 00:20:49,860
I just want to spend
some alone time with you

293
00:20:50,930 --> 00:20:52,340
at the place we first met.

294
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:03,280
Hey.

295
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:04,980
This place is full of safety cams.

296
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:05,730
What do you think you're doing?

297
00:21:07,730 --> 00:21:11,020
You think a former thief
like me is that careless?

298
00:21:11,050 --> 00:21:12,490
I got it all covered.

299
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:18,490
That means…

300
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,520
We can do whatever the hell
we want and no one will see it?

301
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:28,380
What do you have in mind?

302
00:21:38,690 --> 00:21:40,610
What else is there to do at a bowling alley

303
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:41,980
but play bowling?

304
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:11,490
This is the first time

305
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,290
I'm here with someone.

306
00:22:15,210 --> 00:22:19,180
Happiness shared is happiness doubled.

307
00:22:24,010 --> 00:22:25,180
How many tickets?

308
00:22:25,390 --> 00:22:26,280
Two, please.

309
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:28,120
Alright.

310
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,180
This band is playing
for the last time tonight.

311
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:37,390
We're their last audience.

312
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:39,390
I gotta say

313
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:41,550
it's gonna be a memorable night.

314
00:22:46,220 --> 00:22:47,050
You're right.

315
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:48,400
For me,

316
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:50,860
tonight is certainly going
to be a memorable night.

317
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:01,530
Excuse me.

318
00:23:15,930 --> 00:23:16,680
Fadel.

319
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:20,400
Yeah?

320
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:23,060
I have a confession to make.

321
00:23:23,970 --> 00:23:24,770
What?

322
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,350
Well, I…

323
00:23:29,290 --> 00:23:30,200
What?

324
00:23:30,870 --> 00:23:32,250
I…

325
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:36,880
Just say it.

326
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,880
I don't really like heavy metal.

327
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:49,070
Why the hell did you have to shout that?

328
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,080
You wanna get beat or something?

329
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:01,570
Sorry.

330
00:24:02,910 --> 00:24:04,440
You're not mad at me, are you?

331
00:24:06,140 --> 00:24:07,190
Why would I?

332
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:08,870
I already knew that.

333
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,650
What?

334
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,160
Of course I knew.

335
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:15,900
You only pretended to
like it to get close to me,

336
00:24:18,310 --> 00:24:19,440
but you're not into it.

337
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,970
You're more into pop rock music.

338
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,780
All I want to know is
that you're not mad at me.

339
00:24:29,340 --> 00:24:33,570
You don't have to do
anything to impress me.

340
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,960
I want to see the real you.

341
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:46,240
But still, liars should be punished.

342
00:24:46,570 --> 00:24:47,760
Punished?

343
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:50,100
What do you mean?

344
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,590
Hey, what do you mean by “punished”?

345
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,680
Why am I doing this?

346
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:05,070
You're a fake fan.

347
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:07,300
You gotta blend in.

348
00:25:10,790 --> 00:25:12,790
Some people here don't
wear makeup, you know?

349
00:25:13,270 --> 00:25:15,150
You, for one, don't.

350
00:25:15,170 --> 00:25:16,240
Stay still.

351
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:17,640
You're gonna mess it up.

352
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,600
You know what you're doing?

353
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:24,240
I used to wear the same
makeup as my favorite band.

354
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,970
Then you should put some makeup on, too.

355
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:30,110
A matching makeup.

356
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:32,300
No.

357
00:25:33,390 --> 00:25:35,390
I never wear it in public.

358
00:25:38,170 --> 00:25:39,140
Why not?

359
00:25:40,590 --> 00:25:42,590
If you're sick of sneaking about,

360
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:44,360
you don't have to do it.

361
00:25:45,660 --> 00:25:47,980
How long are you going
to live someone else's life?

362
00:25:52,650 --> 00:25:54,400
What do you think you're doing, Style?

363
00:25:55,370 --> 00:25:56,460
We're outside.

364
00:25:56,490 --> 00:25:57,340
Why not?

365
00:25:57,780 --> 00:25:59,780
No one recognizes me anyway.

366
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,570
Try just being someone you want to be.

367
00:26:03,890 --> 00:26:04,960
We'll do it together.

368
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,720
There's nothing to be afraid of.

369
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:06,980
Hey.

370
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,070
Can I get on your shoulders?

371
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:10,250
You're heavy, you know?

372
00:28:48,490 --> 00:28:49,670
Are you drunk?

373
00:28:50,980 --> 00:28:52,440
How could I be?

374
00:28:52,460 --> 00:28:53,600
I hardly drank.

375
00:28:56,010 --> 00:28:58,670
Hey, you think we're gonna get arrested?

376
00:28:59,260 --> 00:29:00,620
If we are,

377
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:01,980
the charges are gonna be long.

378
00:29:02,380 --> 00:29:06,750
Trespassing, stealing, damage to property,

379
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:08,490
we're literally eating their snacks.

380
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:10,990
We're definitely going to jail.

381
00:29:12,990 --> 00:29:14,300
What should we do, then?

382
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,290
Should we…

383
00:29:18,530 --> 00:29:19,990
get in the car and run?

384
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:22,850
We can just...

385
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:23,550
Hey.

386
00:29:26,530 --> 00:29:28,000
I really can't go with you tonight.

387
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,600
But don't worry.

388
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:39,470
After tomorrow, I'm
quitting at the restaurant,

389
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:41,430
and I'll be free.

390
00:29:41,890 --> 00:29:43,170
More importantly,

391
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,560
I wanna get a cat.

392
00:29:49,400 --> 00:29:51,210
I have one right now, though.

393
00:29:52,630 --> 00:29:53,710
Since when?

394
00:29:54,670 --> 00:29:55,990
Since you came along,

395
00:29:56,010 --> 00:29:56,990
'cause you're my cat.

396
00:29:58,760 --> 00:29:59,960
What nonsense…

397
00:30:02,110 --> 00:30:04,930
Can't you just do what
you said you want to today?

398
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:07,260
Can't you?

399
00:30:09,630 --> 00:30:11,747
I really can't.

400
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,286
Will you try to understand?

401
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,400
I gave Fadel my word about something.

402
00:30:22,970 --> 00:30:24,510
But after that,

403
00:30:25,009 --> 00:30:26,664
you're the only one I'll
make any promises with.

404
00:30:28,781 --> 00:30:31,532
You'll be in all of my plans, Kant.

405
00:30:56,780 --> 00:30:57,963
Will you wait here for me for a sec?

406
00:30:58,420 --> 00:30:59,255
Where are you going?

407
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:00,886
You'll know soon.

408
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,707
It's beautiful.

409
00:31:42,330 --> 00:31:43,403
It is, right?

410
00:31:48,390 --> 00:31:49,975
When I was in your room,

411
00:31:50,012 --> 00:31:51,970
I saw all the northern light posters there.

412
00:31:52,980 --> 00:31:55,790
I thought you might like it.

413
00:31:58,520 --> 00:31:59,901
You're very thoughtful, aren't you?

414
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:00,600
Do you like it?

415
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:02,621
Of course, I do.

416
00:32:03,427 --> 00:32:04,338
You know,

417
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:06,627
it's been a dream of mine

418
00:32:07,230 --> 00:32:09,230
to see the northern lights in Iceland.

419
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,080
Take a drive around the islands.

420
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:13,864
Watch some waterfalls.

421
00:32:13,895 --> 00:32:15,230
Get in a hot bath.

422
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,230
I want to see the real puffins, too.

423
00:32:19,690 --> 00:32:20,972
Puffins?

424
00:32:21,003 --> 00:32:22,406
Yeah, you know them?

425
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:23,673
What are they?

426
00:32:23,704 --> 00:32:25,335
They're like penguins,

427
00:32:25,366 --> 00:32:27,372
but with their orange beaks.

428
00:32:27,396 --> 00:32:28,947
They're adorbs.

429
00:32:28,978 --> 00:32:30,940
Now you make me want to see them, too.

430
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,427
If we're lucky,

431
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,864
maybe we can go together.

432
00:32:37,410 --> 00:32:38,633
Of course we can.

433
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,261
How many days should we spend there?

434
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:42,360
10?

435
00:32:44,620 --> 00:32:46,400
I think 15.

436
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,587
Can we make it a road trip?

437
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,784
I'll drive.

438
00:32:54,140 --> 00:32:56,369
I'll make a playlist for the road.

439
00:32:57,150 --> 00:32:57,852
Perfect.

440
00:32:58,818 --> 00:33:00,406
I'll go anywhere

441
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,206
as long as I'm with you.

442
00:34:28,301 --> 00:34:29,021
Hey.

443
00:34:29,249 --> 00:34:30,627
Mind taking a photo with us?

444
00:34:30,650 --> 00:34:31,563
I love your band.

445
00:34:31,581 --> 00:34:32,360
I love you so much.

446
00:34:32,369 --> 00:34:33,710
Gimme a hug.

447
00:34:35,290 --> 00:34:36,960
Let's make it rock 'n roll, guys!

448
00:34:40,504 --> 00:34:41,643
One more.

449
00:34:45,827 --> 00:34:47,640
Some selfies, too, please.

450
00:34:52,123 --> 00:34:53,206
Thank you.

451
00:34:53,827 --> 00:34:54,640
Thank you.

452
00:35:07,410 --> 00:35:10,098
Thanks for coming with me.

453
00:35:12,700 --> 00:35:13,981
If it weren't for you,

454
00:35:14,018 --> 00:35:15,446
I'd probably have sat alone over there.

455
00:35:17,470 --> 00:35:18,510
It's alright.

456
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:22,621
It makes me happy just seeing your smile.

457
00:35:27,323 --> 00:35:28,596
You wanna come over tonight?

458
00:35:29,169 --> 00:35:30,590
I want to cuddle you to sleep.

459
00:35:32,683 --> 00:35:33,643
Should I?

460
00:35:34,553 --> 00:35:36,550
Your Dad's home, isn't he?

461
00:35:37,670 --> 00:35:38,498
One more thing,

462
00:35:39,260 --> 00:35:40,473
I've got work tomorrow.

463
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:44,067
What work?

464
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:45,852
Grocery shopping?

465
00:35:45,870 --> 00:35:47,187
I'll help.

466
00:35:48,978 --> 00:35:49,987
It's something else.

467
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:53,040
You're doing a lot of
second jobs, aren't you?

468
00:35:53,690 --> 00:35:56,332
What else do you do
besides working as a host?

469
00:35:56,830 --> 00:35:58,676
You can tell me.

470
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:00,418
I won't judge.

471
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,556
It's personal.

472
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:11,969
I'm helping someone else out.

473
00:36:12,430 --> 00:36:13,698
You don't need to know any of that.

474
00:36:14,980 --> 00:36:16,664
I'll tell you when I'm ready.

475
00:36:19,107 --> 00:36:21,100
What? What's wrong?

476
00:36:22,770 --> 00:36:24,443
It's just tonight.

477
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,966
You act like we're not going
to see each other again.

478
00:36:30,424 --> 00:36:32,420
It's been a good night.

479
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,427
I don't want it to end.

480
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:39,704
When I'm back,

481
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,449
there'll be more nights like this.

482
00:36:45,830 --> 00:36:46,910
Promise?

483
00:37:10,726 --> 00:37:12,344
I'm very happy tonight.

484
00:37:15,990 --> 00:37:17,550
Me, too.

485
00:37:50,252 --> 00:37:51,587
How long is this gonna take?

486
00:38:01,292 --> 00:38:02,615
Don't ask.

487
00:38:02,630 --> 00:38:03,901
Better to just get it done and over with.

488
00:38:03,926 --> 00:38:05,420
I'm too tired for this.

489
00:38:25,420 --> 00:38:26,510
RUERAT FOUNDATION FOR EDUCATION

490
00:38:36,067 --> 00:38:36,990
Alright.

491
00:38:37,015 --> 00:38:38,092
Please make yourself comfortable.

492
00:38:38,116 --> 00:38:38,633
I'm going to go get ready.

493
00:38:38,652 --> 00:38:39,581
Thank you.

494
00:38:56,540 --> 00:38:57,975
Keep an eye on them.

495
00:38:58,510 --> 00:39:00,184
I'm pretty sure they're
going to do it today,

496
00:39:00,221 --> 00:39:01,513
like Kant said they would.

497
00:39:01,544 --> 00:39:02,535
Yes, Captain.

498
00:39:08,090 --> 00:39:09,390
Oh, little bear!

499
00:39:09,427 --> 00:39:12,110
How adorable!

500
00:39:12,135 --> 00:39:14,769
Let's take a photo together.

501
00:39:16,449 --> 00:39:18,440
What an adorable bear.

502
00:39:18,467 --> 00:39:19,796
One photo, please.

503
00:39:19,821 --> 00:39:21,378
Over here.

504
00:39:21,390 --> 00:39:23,070
Stand in the middle.

505
00:39:24,935 --> 00:39:26,424
You should go over there.

506
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:28,701
Let me see.

507
00:39:35,286 --> 00:39:36,855
Thank you for coming.

508
00:39:41,970 --> 00:39:43,132
Can I have a photo, please?

509
00:39:46,930 --> 00:39:47,864
Can you take it for me?

510
00:39:49,550 --> 00:39:50,430
Babe?

511
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,080
Mr. Bear?

512
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:57,495
This way.

513
00:40:01,190 --> 00:40:02,780
Boy, it's time.

514
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:03,298
This way, please.

515
00:40:03,316 --> 00:40:03,975
Yes.

516
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,920
Wait, hold on.

517
00:40:11,944 --> 00:40:13,200
I want another photo.

518
00:40:13,218 --> 00:40:14,541
That one wasn't very good.

519
00:40:14,572 --> 00:40:15,993
Take one, please.

520
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:19,292
Ugh, lady, quit it already!

521
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:22,190
Hello.

522
00:40:22,221 --> 00:40:29,495
Welcome to the Ruerat Foundation's
charity for better education.

523
00:40:29,526 --> 00:40:33,570
Tonight's event begins with a surprise.

524
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:39,009
We're revealing the newest mascot, which
will be on the Ruerat Foundation's logo.

525
00:40:39,021 --> 00:40:42,633
Please welcome Handsome Bear!

526
00:41:37,686 --> 00:41:39,329
Fadel, don't do it now.

527
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:53,975
Babe, get out of there!

528
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,643
Babe!

529
00:42:16,580 --> 00:42:17,286
Bison.

530
00:42:17,304 --> 00:42:17,969
Run!

531
00:42:19,710 --> 00:42:20,504
Hurry!

532
00:42:20,523 --> 00:42:21,538
They're here!

533
00:42:21,556 --> 00:42:22,258
Quickly!

534
00:42:22,283 --> 00:42:23,255
Follow them!

535
00:42:28,890 --> 00:42:29,790
Police!

536
00:42:29,821 --> 00:42:30,935
Everyone, on the ground.

537
00:42:47,290 --> 00:42:48,516
Go over there.

538
00:42:48,535 --> 00:42:49,889
You, check out that way.

539
00:43:01,180 --> 00:43:02,849
What the hell did you do that for?

540
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:05,483
I missed that shot because of you.

541
00:43:09,852 --> 00:43:11,850
But Babe could get hurt.

542
00:43:11,993 --> 00:43:13,003
Babe who?

543
00:43:13,870 --> 00:43:14,750
Who is he?

544
00:43:18,620 --> 00:43:19,975
A student at the event.

545
00:43:20,012 --> 00:43:21,058
He's Kant's brother.

546
00:43:25,700 --> 00:43:26,935
I was aiming for Ruerat.

547
00:43:27,930 --> 00:43:29,353
You think I'd kill a kid?

548
00:43:31,350 --> 00:43:33,350
He could have gotten caught in the fire.

549
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:36,603
Did I ever miss my shot?

550
00:43:37,550 --> 00:43:40,812
You ended up mixing
personal business with work.

551
00:43:42,390 --> 00:43:43,360
Well?

552
00:43:43,820 --> 00:43:45,040
We're ruined!

553
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:47,987
I'm sorry.

554
00:43:48,652 --> 00:43:49,544
Enough of that.

555
00:43:50,880 --> 00:43:51,975
Let's get back and recoup.

556
00:44:01,870 --> 00:44:03,870
And come up with how
to break this to Mother.

557
00:44:15,021 --> 00:44:16,369
I got super lucky.

558
00:44:16,763 --> 00:44:18,467
The bear mascot saved my life.

559
00:44:19,980 --> 00:44:21,556
Did you see the man inside the bear suit?

560
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,163
No.

561
00:44:23,630 --> 00:44:25,975
I only saw him run after the other mascot.

562
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:29,920
I'm glad you're safe.

563
00:44:34,360 --> 00:44:35,021
Babe.

564
00:44:35,550 --> 00:44:37,716
Can you grab some coffee
for me from next door?

565
00:44:37,956 --> 00:44:38,787
Of course.

566
00:44:45,101 --> 00:44:46,344
Crap.

567
00:44:47,100 --> 00:44:50,332
To think my brother
nearly died because of that.

568
00:44:51,090 --> 00:44:51,975
I think…

569
00:44:52,930 --> 00:44:54,498
Bison saved him.

570
00:44:55,820 --> 00:44:57,716
You think Fadel would shoot Babe?

571
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:01,981
You think he knows you're a snitch?

572
00:45:05,550 --> 00:45:06,775
I don't think so.

573
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:08,584
I've been pretty lowkey.

574
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:12,713
But well,

575
00:45:12,744 --> 00:45:13,963
my work here is over.

576
00:45:14,510 --> 00:45:16,510
I'm done being a snitch.

577
00:45:34,150 --> 00:45:35,507
I want to see Fadel.

578
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:37,027
Style.

579
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:40,744
You have to get over it.

580
00:45:41,286 --> 00:45:43,280
You can't ever get together with him.

581
00:45:43,780 --> 00:45:44,800
Move on.

582
00:45:46,330 --> 00:45:48,621
It'll become a funny
story for your children later

583
00:45:48,916 --> 00:45:50,307
about how you once dated a hitman.

584
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:12,400
We're sorry, Mother,

585
00:46:13,210 --> 00:46:14,781
for messing up this mission.

586
00:46:16,330 --> 00:46:17,729
Did anyone get hurt?

587
00:46:18,260 --> 00:46:19,156
No.

588
00:46:21,150 --> 00:46:22,412
We ran immediately.

589
00:46:23,070 --> 00:46:24,307
Nobody saw us.

590
00:46:25,470 --> 00:46:26,923
Then that's good.

591
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:29,956
I just can't believe

592
00:46:30,690 --> 00:46:32,393
you two would mess up

593
00:46:33,440 --> 00:46:34,603
such an important job.

594
00:46:36,480 --> 00:46:38,480
We might have been a little careless.

595
00:46:39,163 --> 00:46:41,606
We haven't figured out how
the cops knew to be there.

596
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:47,963
I think you just didn't
take it seriously enough.

597
00:46:48,310 --> 00:46:50,246
You weren't on the field with us.

598
00:46:50,270 --> 00:46:51,809
What would you even know?

599
00:46:52,810 --> 00:46:54,221
All you do is sit your ass in an office.

600
00:46:54,233 --> 00:46:55,243
What the hell do you ever do?

601
00:46:55,273 --> 00:46:56,283
Bison!

602
00:46:59,150 --> 00:47:00,609
I don't see it the same way.

603
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:05,120
The police would never find out about this

604
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:07,366
unless they got some tip off

605
00:47:08,061 --> 00:47:10,060
about the time and place.

606
00:47:13,710 --> 00:47:17,095
Is there anyone suspicious
in your life right now?

607
00:47:20,836 --> 00:47:22,073
No, there isn't.

608
00:47:23,870 --> 00:47:26,824
We barely talk or reveal
ourselves to anyone.

609
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:30,818
There are only the
customers at the burger joint

610
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:33,975
that we have to talk to to put up the act.

611
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:36,818
Maybe you're overlooking someone.

612
00:47:37,350 --> 00:47:38,756
Someone you can't bring
yourselves to suspect.

613
00:47:41,860 --> 00:47:42,670
Never mind.

614
00:47:43,827 --> 00:47:48,393
I'll have someone make
sure this news doesn't get out.

615
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,483
But I have to warn you,

616
00:47:52,313 --> 00:47:53,452
he's alive,

617
00:47:54,010 --> 00:47:56,307
and he can come back
to hurt us at any moment.

618
00:47:57,100 --> 00:47:58,707
It wouldn't hurt to be careful.

619
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:05,335
I've always told you

620
00:48:06,470 --> 00:48:08,553
how we can never know someone truly.

621
00:48:10,460 --> 00:48:11,470
The closer you are,

622
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:13,089
the less you see.

623
00:48:17,690 --> 00:48:19,969
Make sure you find that suspicious someone

624
00:48:20,590 --> 00:48:21,870
and take them out.

625
00:48:26,061 --> 00:48:27,846
Before this messes all of us up.

626
00:49:05,489 --> 00:49:06,849
You really think it's them?

627
00:49:13,981 --> 00:49:15,980
Besides customers,

628
00:49:16,689 --> 00:49:18,680
they're the only two people around us.

629
00:49:23,180 --> 00:49:24,787
Kant? A police informant?

630
00:49:27,100 --> 00:49:28,412
And Style as well?

631
00:49:33,050 --> 00:49:34,449
It's all possible.

632
00:49:35,796 --> 00:49:37,790
We need to suspect everyone right now.

633
00:49:40,787 --> 00:49:41,790
What do you want to do?

634
00:49:43,340 --> 00:49:45,120
Should we go back to the restaurant

635
00:49:45,150 --> 00:49:45,987
or should we run?

636
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:49,556
How about my parents' place on that island?

637
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:51,704
We can lay low there.

638
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:00,523
How about…

639
00:50:02,990 --> 00:50:04,295
We go back to the restaurant

640
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:07,544
and act normal.

641
00:50:09,910 --> 00:50:11,273
Just be more careful.

642
00:50:15,840 --> 00:50:16,996
After this,

643
00:50:19,372 --> 00:50:21,009
I'll keep my eyes on them.

644
00:50:21,956 --> 00:50:23,950
If you found out they're the snitches,

645
00:50:25,470 --> 00:50:26,486
what would you do?

646
00:50:34,676 --> 00:50:36,061
What I always do.

647
00:50:43,378 --> 00:50:44,356
Kill them.

648
00:50:57,200 --> 00:50:58,024
It's closed.

649
00:51:28,330 --> 00:51:29,513
Whose cat is that?

650
00:51:30,570 --> 00:51:33,095
He's too chubby to be a stray.

651
00:51:34,380 --> 00:51:35,753
Bison's cat.

652
00:51:35,784 --> 00:51:37,095
He always feeds the little guy.

653
00:51:39,600 --> 00:51:41,600
I guess he misses Bison, then.

654
00:51:42,210 --> 00:51:43,526
He's a food source, after all.

655
00:51:48,320 --> 00:51:49,975
I think you should take him in, Kant.

656
00:51:50,953 --> 00:51:52,950
Yeah, I will.

657
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:55,969
We gave them enough trouble.

658
00:51:56,890 --> 00:51:58,553
I don't want this cat to get
dragged into this mess, too.

659
00:52:06,110 --> 00:52:08,233
Why do I have a feeling
that this isn't over?

660
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:09,969
What do you mean?

661
00:52:10,950 --> 00:52:13,526
They can't run forever, that's for sure.

662
00:52:13,833 --> 00:52:15,673
If they haven't completed their mission,
they will definitely come back.

663
00:52:17,030 --> 00:52:18,621
I guess you're right.

664
00:52:19,130 --> 00:52:20,553
Before things went down,

665
00:52:20,584 --> 00:52:22,966
you saw how attached they were to us.

666
00:52:27,960 --> 00:52:29,218
Who knows?

667
00:52:29,950 --> 00:52:31,710
No matter how much you love someone,

668
00:52:32,627 --> 00:52:34,620
you gotta prioritize saving
your own butts, right?

669
00:52:41,083 --> 00:52:42,418
Hey, there.

670
00:52:46,012 --> 00:52:48,990
ONE WEEK LATER

671
00:53:09,050 --> 00:53:10,510
I was thinking of going to your place.

672
00:53:10,890 --> 00:53:12,412
But you were more impatient than me, huh?

673
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:15,015
Where have you been?

674
00:53:15,409 --> 00:53:16,793
You didn't reply to any of my texts.

675
00:53:17,680 --> 00:53:19,520
My phone broke.

676
00:53:19,556 --> 00:53:21,304
I had to change both my
phone and my number.

677
00:53:22,770 --> 00:53:23,753
I was busy, too.

678
00:53:24,410 --> 00:53:26,578
And you didn't think
to contact me a little?

679
00:53:27,210 --> 00:53:29,353
I was worried sick about you, you know?

680
00:53:30,950 --> 00:53:32,449
I was out of town.

681
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:34,683
But I'm here now, aren't I?

682
00:53:34,707 --> 00:53:35,963
What are you complaining about now?

683
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:37,987
Sit down.

684
00:53:38,370 --> 00:53:39,556
I'll whip up something in the kitchen.

685
00:53:41,753 --> 00:53:43,267
Anything you'd like to eat?

686
00:53:47,050 --> 00:53:47,760
Anything's fine.

687
00:53:47,790 --> 00:53:48,793
You decide.

688
00:53:49,249 --> 00:53:50,790
Everything you make is good anyway.

689
00:53:51,540 --> 00:53:52,990
You sure are a sweet talker.

690
00:53:54,240 --> 00:53:55,230
What do you want?

691
00:53:56,646 --> 00:53:58,209
Did you do something wrong?

692
00:53:59,840 --> 00:54:00,873
No.

693
00:54:01,980 --> 00:54:03,735
I just really missed you.

694
00:54:04,430 --> 00:54:06,264
Is it so weird to get
a little affectionate?

695
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:10,935
You know, all this time apart

696
00:54:10,960 --> 00:54:14,720
really frustrated me.

697
00:54:25,033 --> 00:54:25,809
Stop it.

698
00:54:27,420 --> 00:54:28,609
I said stop.

699
00:54:30,510 --> 00:54:31,796
Not here.

700
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:36,867
Well, how about some spaghetti?

701
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:38,860
Okay.

702
00:54:55,230 --> 00:54:57,969
You'll be in all of my plans, Kant.

703
00:54:59,250 --> 00:55:00,658
I'll go anywhere

704
00:55:01,230 --> 00:55:02,227
as long as I'm with you.

705
00:55:10,010 --> 00:55:11,230
Slow down.

706
00:55:11,575 --> 00:55:13,570
You'll just pass out drunk
at the bar at this rate.

707
00:55:19,870 --> 00:55:20,787
Bison.

708
00:55:28,970 --> 00:55:30,240
Where have you been?

709
00:55:30,264 --> 00:55:31,686
I couldn't reach you at all.

710
00:55:33,070 --> 00:55:34,104
Sorry.

711
00:55:34,670 --> 00:55:36,941
I was out of town on
an errand with Fadel.

712
00:55:37,950 --> 00:55:39,230
I see.

713
00:55:40,890 --> 00:55:42,129
What kind of errand?

714
00:55:42,550 --> 00:55:43,747
Did anything happen?

715
00:55:45,920 --> 00:55:47,649
It's just some petty family issue.

716
00:55:47,661 --> 00:55:48,941
Never mind that.

717
00:55:50,220 --> 00:55:51,390
What about you?

718
00:55:51,729 --> 00:55:53,390
Drinking beer all alone like this…

719
00:55:55,240 --> 00:55:56,400
Anything weighing on your mind?

720
00:55:59,460 --> 00:56:01,015
If there's anything weighing on my mind,

721
00:56:01,830 --> 00:56:03,956
it's gotta be you disappearing on me.

722
00:56:04,460 --> 00:56:05,698
Were you worried about me?

723
00:56:10,560 --> 00:56:13,126
Who else would I be worried
about if not my boyfriend?

724
00:56:30,040 --> 00:56:31,033
Oh, hey.

725
00:56:32,360 --> 00:56:35,526
I adopted the black cat you always fed.

726
00:56:35,950 --> 00:56:38,806
I went to see you at the
restaurant and he was just here.

727
00:56:39,600 --> 00:56:40,910
I didn't want him to starve.

728
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:48,929
Thank you

729
00:56:49,667 --> 00:56:51,286
for remembering what I love.

730
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:01,809
OLD FART

731
00:57:08,020 --> 00:57:08,941
Who was that?

732
00:57:09,249 --> 00:57:10,363
Don't you have to take the call?

733
00:57:13,140 --> 00:57:14,615
Just someone who wants a tattoo.

734
00:57:15,187 --> 00:57:17,353
He keeps changing his mind about the tatt.

735
00:57:17,378 --> 00:57:18,861
I don't want to talk to him anymore.

736
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:21,550
I want to talk to you more.

737
00:57:23,950 --> 00:57:27,372
How about we drink and go back to my place?

738
00:57:28,250 --> 00:57:29,446
I can't.

739
00:57:29,470 --> 00:57:31,003
I have work later.

740
00:57:31,532 --> 00:57:33,530
I just showed up here
because I wanted to see you.

741
00:57:40,100 --> 00:57:41,464
I have to go.

742
00:57:41,483 --> 00:57:42,892
Fadel is gonna have
my head if I'm late.

743
00:57:44,490 --> 00:57:45,550
Okay.

744
00:57:46,300 --> 00:57:49,421
Please don't just
disappear like that again.

745
00:57:54,230 --> 00:57:54,972
Bye.

746
00:58:29,304 --> 00:58:29,993
Hey.

747
00:58:30,820 --> 00:58:32,369
You don't have to help.

748
00:58:32,393 --> 00:58:33,390
I'll clean up later.

749
00:58:34,140 --> 00:58:35,267
Come on.

750
00:58:35,280 --> 00:58:36,738
You fed me.

751
00:58:36,750 --> 00:58:37,993
Think of my service as payment.

752
00:58:49,210 --> 00:58:49,975
Hello.

753
00:58:51,180 --> 00:58:51,969
Yeah, Bison?

754
00:58:53,400 --> 00:58:54,566
Hang on.

755
00:59:32,010 --> 00:59:34,418
Oh, what's with the music?

756
00:59:34,424 --> 00:59:35,421
We're closed, aren't we?

757
00:59:35,766 --> 00:59:37,420
Can't I get a little romantic?

758
00:59:38,450 --> 00:59:40,689
You were just calling me
out for being affectionate.

759
00:59:40,720 --> 00:59:41,981
Now you wanna be romantic?

760
00:59:44,330 --> 00:59:45,944
What did Bison say?

761
00:59:46,850 --> 00:59:47,969
Is he with Kant?

762
00:59:49,120 --> 00:59:49,876
Yeah.

763
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:52,443
Said he'd be home late.

764
00:59:53,910 --> 00:59:55,249
He must really have missed Kant.

765
00:59:58,060 --> 00:59:59,243
I've missed you.

766
01:00:00,650 --> 01:00:03,950
I've got no one messing with me
when you're not there.

767
01:00:06,000 --> 01:00:07,563
So I'm just annoying you.

768
01:00:08,300 --> 01:00:09,569
Is that even a good thing?

769
01:00:09,778 --> 01:00:10,787
It is.

770
01:00:12,520 --> 01:00:16,141
Having someone to miss is good.

771
01:00:17,729 --> 01:00:19,720
It makes me want to go grocery shopping

772
01:00:20,160 --> 01:00:21,723
and go jogging

773
01:00:22,540 --> 01:00:23,956
with the hopes of running into you.

774
01:00:29,400 --> 01:00:31,969
Are we officially entering
romantic territory?

775
01:00:32,646 --> 01:00:34,640
I want to do what lovers do.

776
01:00:37,310 --> 01:00:38,406
It's alright.

777
01:00:39,380 --> 01:00:41,741
I don't want you to do
what you don't want to do.

778
01:00:44,530 --> 01:00:46,966
But I can be exactly what you want.

779
01:00:54,350 --> 01:00:55,403
I think…

780
01:00:56,830 --> 01:00:57,975
I'm in love with you.

781
01:01:56,443 --> 01:01:57,243
(Fadel.)

782
01:01:58,670 --> 01:01:59,970
(They're the snitches.)

783
01:03:05,210 --> 01:03:09,864
♪ Go on, hurt me to my core ♪

784
01:03:09,895 --> 01:03:11,304
You have my heart now,

785
01:03:11,784 --> 01:03:12,793
so take good care of it.

786
01:03:12,818 --> 01:03:20,129
♪ Flames in the hand are burning ♪

787
01:03:20,135 --> 01:03:23,981
♪ From head to toe, the
heat is all consuming ♪

788
01:03:24,006 --> 01:03:28,923
♪ Splash water on me ♪

789
01:03:28,953 --> 01:03:33,987
♪ Hurt me please, dearest love ♪

790
01:03:34,940 --> 01:03:39,458
♪ Hurt me please, can't get enough ♪

791
01:03:44,080 --> 01:03:46,080
(Next Week)
I'm happy just having a boyfriend like you.

792
01:03:46,110 --> 01:03:47,021
Ever since I met you,

793
01:03:47,040 --> 01:03:48,332
I've gotten to know a
different side of myself.

794
01:03:48,350 --> 01:03:50,178
You're serious about him, aren't you?

795
01:03:51,704 --> 01:03:53,187
Cheers!

796
01:03:56,190 --> 01:03:57,144
Bison!

797
01:03:58,150 --> 01:04:00,726
We still have to see the
northern lights together.

798
01:04:01,218 --> 01:04:02,566
I'm arresting the little one.

799
01:04:02,621 --> 01:04:03,766
If you don't want to get in trouble,

800
01:04:03,796 --> 01:04:05,600
go home and be with your brother.

801
01:04:05,630 --> 01:04:06,283
Hey.

802
01:04:06,695 --> 01:04:07,747
Hey!
